			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;[Please summarize the enhancement so it will be comprehensible to someone&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;from outside the Native Client team. A good summary will include:]&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Currently, it is somewhat hard to test coverage of the validators, in that we don't have a good way to filter instructions tested in private_tests, based on the validator.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
It is hard to test replacements to the decoder/validator without better filtering of what instructions are effected.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Make an API that allows us to test a single instruction if:
(1) The instruction is NaCl legal in terms of prefix bytes and opcode.
(2) The instruction validates except for multi-line patterns.
(3) The instruction validates including multi-line patterns.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
When x86-32 and x86-64 implement these API's.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Better testing facilities for changes to the  x86 decoder/validator.
